1
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,750
[KANADE]
I'll never lose!

2
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,041
That's impossible!

3
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:43,541
Justice cannot die!

4
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:45,916
[TOM]
Always so naive!

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,458
There's no justice! It's a lie!

6
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,916
Which one? Who will it be?

7
00:01:03,458 --> 00:01:05,208
Kanade!

8
00:01:09,958 --> 00:01:11,000
I'm done!

9
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:17,875
Tom! Tom is the winner!

10
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:20,125
--You're wrong.
--Huh?

11
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:22,833
The real winner... is love.

12
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:30,208
[GIN]
Hey, look! A pile of poo!

13
00:01:34,291 --> 00:01:37,291
[TOM] Heck yeah!
That was awesome!

14
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:38,291
[GIN]
So cool!

15
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:39,958
Next time,
let's do space robots!

16
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,166
[TOM]
Yeah!

17
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,875
[laughing]

18
00:01:43,958 --> 00:01:46,083
"Love," huh...

19
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:30,708
[KAHO] Thank you
so much for everything.

20
00:03:30,791 --> 00:03:32,291
[GUARD 7A]
Get home safe, now.

21
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:33,625
[KAHO]
Yes, sir.

22
00:03:37,666 --> 00:03:39,083
[KAHO] Thank you,
and I'm sorry you had

23
00:03:39,166 --> 00:03:41,625
to come and get me,
Mr. Takahashi.

24
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:42,916
No, it's okay.

25
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,625
Can you tell me why
you were snooping around

26
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,333
an elementary school, though?

27
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,625
Poor Kaho's in a tough spot.

28
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:07,625
And she can't
even talk about it.

29
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:20,458
[CHIAKI]
Ignored by her ex-boyfriend

30
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:23,625
and mistaken for a stalker?

31
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:26,291
[SHUGO]
It's complicated, huh?

32
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:31,375
Oh! I forgot. Someone
called for you from home.

33
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:33,958
They said you weren't
answering your phone.

34
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:35,541
It seemed pretty urgent, too.

35
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:40,916
Yeah, I'd definitely
call that pretty urgent.

36
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,500
You have telegrams, as well.

37
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:47,791
Who sends telegrams?

38
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:50,333
Wow, I should probably
give him a call real quick.

39
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:57,666
[screaming]

40
00:04:57,750 --> 00:05:00,083
[CHIAKI]
Well, that's not disturbing!

41
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:02,833
[KAHO]
I, um... I need to go home.

42
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,083
[TOM]
Hey, Kanade!

43
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:18,125
What was your deal
in dodge ball earlier?

44
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:19,875
You went down
in the first round!

45
00:05:19,958 --> 00:05:21,333
That's not like you at all!

46
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:25,625
I have something I
would like to add to that.

47
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:27,625
What is this crap?

48
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:30,333
You're the best when it comes
to serving fair lunch portions,

49
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:32,291
but you're way off today, man.

50
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:33,458
Two carrots?

51
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,458
How could you do that to me?

52
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:37,125
[GIN]
Are you a pod person?

53
00:05:39,958 --> 00:05:42,875
You guys are right.
Something's off.

54
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:45,583
I can't say I'm
quite myself, either.

55
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:48,166
It seems to me that we're
suffering from the same thing.

56
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:53,666
[KAZ] Kanade, you're
lovesick, aren't you?

57
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:58,083
I thought he broke up
with that one girl, though!

58
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,916
You mean there
might be a new girl?

59
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,875
--Well, look at the play-ball!
--For real.

60
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:03,916
[KAZ]
You're thinking "playboy"!

61
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,583
Like Hanako?

62
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,083
[KAZ]
Who is Hanako?

63
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:09,000
Hey! Are you listening to me?

64
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:10,250
Who's Hanako?

65
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,625
[KANADE]
Kaho...

66
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:25,250
Do you get what's going on
with him? Because I sure don't.

67
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:27,083
Not at all.
But at times like these,

68
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,750
there's only one thing to do!

69
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:32,541
The Ten Time Quiz!

70
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:35,333
Yum-yum eat-'em-up,
hooray!

71
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:38,833
Kanade, say the word
"rest" ten times.

72
00:06:38,916 --> 00:06:41,833
[KANADE]
Rest, rest, rest, rest, rest,

73
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,791
rest, rest, rest...

74
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,791
[NARRATOR]
In the "Ten Time Quiz" game,

75
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,708
one person makes another say
a given word ten times

76
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:52,041
then asks a question
to provoke an incorrect,

77
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:54,458
yet amusing response.

78
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,625
It is said to have its
roots in ancient Rome,

79
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:59,666
where a restaurateur challenged
his customers with "Venus"

80
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,333
and would then jab
them with his elbow

81
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:04,208
when they inevitably
failed to say "wenus."

82
00:07:06,041 --> 00:07:08,125
Rest and rest.

83
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,000
Nice. Now add a B to it.

84
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:12,166
So, rest-buh?

85
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:15,208
[GIN]
No, it's breast!

86
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:16,208
Say breast!

87
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:17,416
[TOM]
Are you kidding me?

88
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,416
Kanade just got it wrong!

89
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:20,791
[laughing]

90
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:21,666
[KAZ]
Kanade.

91
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:23,833
[TOM]
What an idiot!

92
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,208
[laughing]

93
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:26,833
[TOM, GIN]
Rest-buh!

94
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:29,125
--[KANADE] I'm home.
--[KAZ] Pardon us.

95
00:07:29,208 --> 00:07:30,208
Hey, Kanade.

96
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:31,666
We're having your
favorite tonight:

97
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,791
batter-fried fishcake
and seaweed.

98
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:36,083
Aren't you supposed to
gargle when you get home?

99
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,416
Anyone know what's
going on with him?

100
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,708
Maybe. I think he
must be lovesick.

101
00:07:46,791 --> 00:07:48,500
Everyone can tell
something's up.

102
00:07:48,583 --> 00:07:49,750
That's not normal Kanade.

103
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,458
I followed him home
to see if I could help.

104
00:07:51,541 --> 00:07:53,750
But I don't know what to do.

105
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,208
Well, what can you do?

106
00:07:55,291 --> 00:07:56,916
Love is a rough business.

107
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:04,250
"Children's Telephone Helpline"?

108
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,791
[KAZ] You mean a kid can
simply call this number,

109
00:08:06,875 --> 00:08:10,000
and a grown-up will help them
answer all their questions?

110
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:11,416
No way! All of them?

111
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:14,708
That's awesome!
Let's call for help, you guys!

112
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:18,208
[KAZ] They help you
with your problems?

113
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:19,375
Kanade!

114
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:21,583
Don't you have something
you'd like to ask?

115
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:23,125
What? Me?

116
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:26,208
Oh! I so know what
I wanna ask a grown-up!

117
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:27,875
--You do?
--Yep.

118
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:30,625
[KANADE] Okay, we can
borrow my dad's phone!

119
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:31,708
[GIN, TOM]
Yeah!

120
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:33,458
We got 'em!

121
00:08:33,541 --> 00:08:35,041
This might be a good thing.

122
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:37,083
And they seem like
they're interested.

123
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:38,541
When you first
mentioned wanting us

124
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:40,666
to run a children's
telephone hotline,

125
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,041
I wasn't sure what to expect.

126
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:45,000
I just wanted to
help those boys out.

127
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:47,333
They're all so worried
about Kanade, you know.

128
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:48,750
Right, sure you did.

129
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,833
I wonder if that precious Kaz
will call anytime soon.

130
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:52,583
I've got something
I'd love to ask him!

131
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:53,916
Love to ask...

132
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,583
What? Aren't the kids
supposed to do the asking?

133
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:58,708
There's no way
that this ends well.

134
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:02,375
[phone ringing]

135
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,625
Uh, hello?

136
00:09:06,125 --> 00:09:07,291
Excuse me, sir.

137
00:09:07,375 --> 00:09:09,458
Have I reached the
Children's Helpline?

138
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:11,375
[ARASHI]
It's Kaz! I wasn't ready!

139
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:13,416
[screaming]

140
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,166
[KAZ]
Um, are you still there?

141
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:22,625
Tell me. What kind of
underwear do you have on?

142
00:09:23,666 --> 00:09:25,125
So what happened, Kaz?

143
00:09:25,208 --> 00:09:27,125
I must have dialed
the wrong number.

144
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:29,083
'Cause I got a pervert.

145
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:30,875
[KOTA] Arashi, don't tell me
that's what you wanted

146
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:32,291
to ask him!

147
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:34,416
[ARASHI]
It was instinct. I'm sorry.

148
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,666
You're the worst!

149
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,333
Those kids are taking
this hotline seriously.

150
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:38,500
Why can't you?

151
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:40,083
Next time, I will
answer the phone call!

152
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,875
[phone ringing]

153
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:51,041
[KOTA] Um, hello,
Children's Telephone Helpline.

154
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,375
I have a question!

155
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:53,625
Which is softer?

156
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:56,583
A rest-buh, or a real breast,
or a cream puff?

157
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,375
Ah, boobies.
I want a close encounter.

158
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:02,166
What? No one cares
about that stuff.

159
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,083
Yuh-huh!

160
00:10:03,166 --> 00:10:05,291
[KAZ]
I agree. That's boring.

161
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:06,708
[TOM]
How do you know?

162
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:09,416
Don't tell me you can
already answer that question!

163
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:11,000
Can you? Have you touched any?

164
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:14,083
Do you know which one is softer?
Why haven't you answered me?!

165
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:16,666
[KAZ] No! Look, I...
I don't know! Leave me alone!

166
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:20,166
Fishy... Normally,
you'd talk more fancy.

167
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:22,500
No way.

168
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,916
You seriously took the
highway up to Nipple Town?

169
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,666
[KAZ]
No, I didn't take any highways!

170
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,666
I just bumped into them, okay?

171
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:32,250
Oh, my God.
This is so awkward.

172
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:35,958
Need to stop this conversation.
Oh, right. Goodbye kids.

173
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:39,666
[TAGA]
So what happened, Kota?

174
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:42,041
Huh? Nothing...
He just bumped into them!

175
00:10:42,125 --> 00:10:43,250
Lucky!

176
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,083
I'd love to have a go
at girl-mode Kota's

177
00:10:45,166 --> 00:10:46,333
sweet little peaches!

178
00:10:46,416 --> 00:10:48,208
I could even take pictures
of them from afar.

179
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:51,375
Play some fun guessing
games like "Pic the Nip!"

180
00:10:51,458 --> 00:10:53,083
[KOTA]
He just bumped into them!

181
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:54,791
Please quit saying
that kind of stuff.

182
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:56,416
I'm asking you to stop nicely!

183
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:57,791
How can you be like this?

184
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,916
What about your girlfriend?
Don't you love Chiaki?

185
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,291
[ARASHI]
Kota.

186
00:11:01,375 --> 00:11:05,625
I love Chiaki more
than anyone in the world.

187
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,875
However...

188
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:10,416
No matter how
much I may love her,

189
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,625
what I desire...

190
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:14,916
...will always be
pretty-girl boys.

191
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,083
Nice try.

192
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:17,541
For a second,
you'd created the illusion

193
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:19,458
of saying something amazing.

194
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,791
Commonly known as
a classic pervert's trick.

195
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:23,250
[ARASHI]
You flatter me.

196
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:26,916
So ask for advice?

197
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,750
[KAZ]
It doesn't have to be.

198
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:31,875
Just what you're thinking.
What's bothering you.

199
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:34,500
Putting all that into words
should help you out a lot.

200
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,916
[phone ringing]

201
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,541
Yes, hello?

202
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:49,333
[KANADE] Is this the Children's
Telephone Helpline?

203
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:51,916
Yeah, sure, how can I help?

204
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,583
[KANADE]
I, uh...

205
00:11:54,666 --> 00:11:57,250
[TAGA]
Yes, you what?

206
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:58,500
Don't overthink it.

207
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:00,375
Just say whatever's
on your mind.

208
00:12:05,875 --> 00:12:07,125
[KANADE]
I thought...

209
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:09,833
I thought I wasn't lonely
with everyone here.

210
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:11,666
Go on.

211
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:13,083
[KANADE]
But I guess I am.

212
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:15,375
You know, lonely.

213
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:16,916
And why is that?

214
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:22,750
[KANADE] I want to talk about
our class killifish laying eggs,

215
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,750
and how the crayfish I
put in the tank ate them all.

216
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:29,000
I wanna talk about Hanako
who lives in the bathroom,

217
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:31,958
about how Gin threw up all
the carrots he ate at lunch.

218
00:12:34,041 --> 00:12:36,416
You can tell me about that.

219
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:39,083
[KANADE]
But I want to tell Kaho.

220
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:44,583
[TAGA] So you say, but aren't
you the one who ignored her?

221
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:46,000
I am, yes.

222
00:12:46,083 --> 00:12:48,958
But I didn't know life
without her would be hell!

223
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:55,291
[TAGA]
What are you saying?

224
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:56,458
[KANADE]
I just can't...

225
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:59,000
I can't stand not
being able to see her!

226
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,083
Um, hello?

227
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:08,666
Look. If you've realized
someone is precious to you,

228
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:10,291
then you should
really tell them.

229
00:13:10,375 --> 00:13:13,666
I'd let them know before it's
too late if I were you.

230
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:14,750
I should tell her?

231
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:16,375
Her, yes! Tell her!

232
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:20,416
[TAGA]
Kaho's not here anymore, though.

233
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,500
[KANADE]
Why not?

234
00:13:22,583 --> 00:13:24,125
Because she went home.

235
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:27,541
Could be you'll
never see her again.

236
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:39,708
[TAGA]
So what's the plan?

237
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:43,041
If you're okay like this,
let it be over and done.

238
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:44,333
But I'm not.

239
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:45,958
[TAGA]
So what's the plan?

240
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:50,625
[KANADE]
I... I'm gonna go get Kaho!

241
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:20,541
[CHIAKI]
So you're really going?

242
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:27,250
I am.

243
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:29,916
You know she's from Kanazawa
in the Hokuriku region, right?

244
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,958
[ARASHI]
That's a 5-hour trip by car.

245
00:14:33,041 --> 00:14:34,625
[CHIAKI]
And yet...

246
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:36,833
...you're gonna get
there on a bike?

247
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:38,250
What's the big deal?

248
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:40,791
If you have your own bike,
then you can go anywhere!

249
00:14:40,875 --> 00:14:42,916
I'm going, too!

250
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,833
A journey is best measured
in friends instead of miles!

251
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:47,125
I'm joining.

252
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,250
Where we're headed,

253
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:50,083
there've been a ton
of UFO sightings!

254
00:14:50,166 --> 00:14:52,875
I'll go and head on home
since Osaka's on the way.

255
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:53,916
Great timin'!

256
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,875
You're not going
that far by bike!

257
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:57,791
It's too dangerous
for kids your age.

258
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,625
Besides, Osaka is in
the other direction,

259
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:01,000
but you're not listening.

260
00:15:01,083 --> 00:15:04,000
Symbolism!
We go fresh! And stinky!

261
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:05,000
[TOM]
Stinky! Yes!

262
00:15:05,083 --> 00:15:06,875
You need to wear this.
Put it on.

263
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:08,625
[KANADE]
Thank you!

264
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:11,208
Okay, see you 'round
and around, propeller!

265
00:15:11,291 --> 00:15:12,708
[GIN, TOM]
Propeller!

266
00:15:12,791 --> 00:15:13,833
[JOJI]
Go!

267
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:20,916
[CHIAKI]
Where are you going, Taga?

268
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,291
[TAGA]
Why does it matter?

269
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,416
You're so sweet.

270
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:45,833
[VENDOR 8A] Care for a boxed
lunch, ice cream, beer, coffee?

271
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:49,000
[KAHO] Excuse me, what kind
of lunches do you have?

272
00:15:49,083 --> 00:15:50,875
[VENDOR 8A]
We have sandwiches and sushi.

273
00:15:50,958 --> 00:15:52,666
Oh, or a seaweed set.

274
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:54,291
[KAHO]
A seaweed set sounds good.

275
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:56,250
Wonderful.
Thank you so much!

276
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:02,333
[KAHO]
Seaweed is Kanade's favorite.

277
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:04,125
[KANADE]
Kaho. Can I have your seaweed?

278
00:16:07,875 --> 00:16:10,000
[KAHO giggles]
All yours.

279
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,416
[KANADE]
Yeah, seaweed!

280
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:14,541
I love seaweed! Seaweed!

281
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:17,125
[KAHO giggling]

282
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:18,291
Three-second rule!

283
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:19,750
Boom, and it's safe!

284
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:25,041
[KANADE]
My wee seaweed buddies!

285
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,416
[KAHO giggling]

286
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:42,416
[KANADE]
First stage: the straightaway!

287
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:44,583
All right, you just
leave them straightaways

288
00:16:44,666 --> 00:16:46,791
to the Naniwa Speed Coaster!

289
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,125
[yells]

290
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:53,208
I tell you what, ain't nobody
fast enough to pass me!

291
00:16:57,291 --> 00:16:59,000
[GIN] Oh, no.
What happened, Speed Coaster?

292
00:16:59,083 --> 00:17:00,500
[JOJI]
I forgot about somethin'.

293
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,833
The one thing that
can cramp my style!

294
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:03,708
[GIN]
What?

295
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,125
[JOJI]
Red lights hate me!

296
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:12,208
It's a long one.

297
00:17:12,291 --> 00:17:13,416
"Against the red."

298
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,708
"If we all cross together,

299
00:17:14,791 --> 00:17:16,000
there's nothing to fear!"

300
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:17,791
[KANADE]
Guys, no!

301
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,625
Kanade, what do you mean "no"?

302
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:21,666
We're trying to get you
there as fast as we can!

303
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,791
[KANADE] What do you mean,
"what do you mean 'no'?"

304
00:17:23,875 --> 00:17:26,083
Come on! Would you crush the
feelings of the crossing guard

305
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:29,083
who keeps us safe and will
also say "have a good day"?

306
00:17:30,458 --> 00:17:31,541
Good point, man.

307
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:33,958
My momma happens
to be a crossing guard.

308
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:36,083
Wish she wouldn't wear yellow
tiger stripes, though.

309
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:38,333
You guys, the light
finally changed.

310
00:17:57,083 --> 00:17:58,375
[ALL]
Yeah!

311
00:17:59,458 --> 00:18:02,000
[KANADE]
Second stage: the slope!

312
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:05,583
I can get up this
monster hill no problem!

313
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:11,583
[BOYS]
Huff, huff, huff, huff...

314
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:13,750
Isn't this always the
part where people drop out

315
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,583
because they've
got heat exhaustion?

316
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:17,833
That's why we
have to have major guts!

317
00:18:18,625 --> 00:18:19,916
[KANADE]
Brother!

318
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,333
[JOJI]
Don't worry about me!

319
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,833
Go! Get the girl!

320
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:27,500
[KANADE]
I'm sorry, Brother!

321
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:32,041
[KANADE]
Third stage: the mountain!

322
00:18:32,125 --> 00:18:34,250
You ready to cross it?

323
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:35,041
[GIN]
What for?

324
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:36,125
[TOM]
A shortcut?

325
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:38,166
No, we go because it's there!

326
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:41,083
Awesome! Ha!

327
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:43,750
[BOYS]
Huff, huff, huff, huff, huff...

328
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,416
Tom!

329
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,750
[yells]

330
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:49,000
You guys okay?

331
00:18:50,166 --> 00:18:51,000
No!

332
00:18:51,083 --> 00:18:52,000
[GIN]
Keep going!

333
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:53,208
[TOM]
Dog poop alert!

334
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,375
[KANADE yelling]

335
00:18:56,458 --> 00:18:57,791
[GIN, TOM]
Kanade!

336
00:18:57,875 --> 00:19:01,750
[KANADE yelling]

337
00:19:16,875 --> 00:19:18,375
[JOJI]
It's no use, huh.

338
00:19:18,458 --> 00:19:19,583
[TOM]
What can you do?

339
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:21,208
We all got flats.

340
00:19:21,291 --> 00:19:24,250
[GIN] Yeah, I gotta get
to cram school anyway.

341
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:26,625
Kanade, let her go, man.

342
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:29,125
I won't give up.

343
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:30,666
I'll never give up!

344
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:32,833
I'll walk there.
I'll even crawl!

345
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:34,041
You can't!

346
00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:40,041
[TAGA] If you want to
go that badly, hop on in.

347
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:43,958
[KANADE]
Taga!

348
00:19:45,375 --> 00:19:47,416
Don't worry about your bike.
I'll take care of it.

349
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,666
[KANADE]
Tom!

350
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:50,916
And never fear.
I'll get to cram school on time!

351
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:51,875
[KANADE]
Gin!

352
00:19:51,958 --> 00:19:53,541
Show her your manly spirit!

353
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,291
[KANADE]
See you later!

354
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:17,958
[KAHO] Home is where
the heart is, right?

355
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:24,291
[KAHO]
Anyone here?

356
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:34,125
[MAN crying]

357
00:20:44,958 --> 00:20:52,416
[MAN crying]

358
00:22:27,041 --> 00:22:29,458
I just got one of
the biggest scoops ever!

359
00:22:30,791 --> 00:22:32,541
According to my big brothers,

360
00:22:32,625 --> 00:22:34,708
if you're going 40 miles
an hour on your bike,

361
00:22:34,791 --> 00:22:36,458
and you do this,
it's supposed to feel

362
00:22:36,541 --> 00:22:38,708
exactly like touching boobies!

363
00:22:38,791 --> 00:22:39,708
--Yeah?
--Cool!

364
00:22:39,791 --> 00:22:40,958
Seriously?

365
00:22:41,041 --> 00:22:42,583
[TOM] Apparently,
it's called "air-petting"!

366
00:22:42,666 --> 00:22:44,791
It's an all-you-can-touch
boobie joyride!

367
00:22:44,875 --> 00:22:46,708
If ya ask me, it's worth a try.

368
00:22:46,791 --> 00:22:49,000
Yeah, but how can
we go that fast?

369
00:22:49,083 --> 00:22:50,333
[ARASHI chuckles]

370
00:22:51,291 --> 00:22:52,666
You can sit back
and let a grown-up

371
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:53,958
show you how it's done.

372
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:55,125
[KANADE]
Good luck, Arashi!

373
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:56,708
[TOM]
You can do it!

374
00:22:56,791 --> 00:23:01,458
[BOYS cheering]

375
00:23:01,541 --> 00:23:03,291
Talk to me, Kaz.

376
00:23:03,375 --> 00:23:04,625
Am I going 40 yet?

377
00:23:04,708 --> 00:23:06,791
Um... Why are you
asking Kaz about that?

378
00:23:06,875 --> 00:23:09,708
[KOTA] Is it because
he's good at numbers?

379
00:23:09,791 --> 00:23:10,958
Not... quite...

380
00:23:11,041 --> 00:23:13,708
I ask... because
Kaz is beautiful!

381
00:23:13,791 --> 00:23:15,166
[moaning]

382
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:16,291
[ARASHI]
Tell me, Kaz.

383
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:18,291
Am I there yet?

384
00:23:18,375 --> 00:23:19,833
Oh, yes!

385
00:23:19,916 --> 00:23:21,958
So close! I'm almost there!

386
00:23:22,041 --> 00:23:23,958
I'm there! I'm so there!

387
00:23:24,041 --> 00:23:25,958
[TAGA]
Shut up!

388
00:23:26,041 --> 00:23:27,666
Owie. Taga...

389
00:23:27,750 --> 00:23:30,916
You know you can kick
me more if you want.

390
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,250
You disgusting pathogen.

391
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:36,416
Great. I'd like to report
a deviant, please.

392
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:38,375
Yes, and hurry.

393
00:23:39,666 --> 00:23:40,750
